                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 3: Foreign entities seeking investment clearance in India may now be asked to furnish details, including their shareholding structure, address of the parent and source of funds, in view of recent taxation issues. The Central Board of Direct Taxes is pressing the Foreign Investment Promotion Board (FIPB) to include additional information from the taxation angle at the time of examining the applications.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 3: Bharat Forge has formed a joint venture with Alstom to manufacture power equipment. The JV will invest Rs 2,400 crore to set up a plant at Mundra in Gujarat.                             
	 New Delhi, Dec. 3: The Reserve Bank today said the financial crisis in Dubai could have some impact on remittances and would affect those parts of the country that receive inflows from the nation in larger quantity.                            
	 London, Dec. 3: The European Central Bank has retained the benchmark rates, continuing with its low interest rate regime to boost the regions economic recovery.                                                                                                                          
